It is easy to admit the fact that Moroccan teenagers in both elementary and secondary school have. One of the most extraordinary problems is lack of ties and relationships among friends and students. In other words, modern Arabic schools hurt self-esteem by ignoring both emotional and psychological development of their pupils, in addition to failing to provide training facilities that can support outstanding students and teachers.
